    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Processes for making photographic prints using a bichromate compound which, when exposed to light, causes its colloid binder to harden; unhardened areas are washed or abraded away. Pigments may be incorporated before exposure or during development. Though the expression dichromate is now preferred in chemistry, bichromate remains common usage in photography.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a sales crómicas de potasio, amonio o sodio (Cr2 O7), llamadas tambien dicromatos. Estos elementos son sensibilizadoras a la luz en asociación con emulsiones organicas. Son muy usadas en procesos fotográficos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pigmentdruk waarbij een bichromaatverbinding wordt gebruikt die, wanneer die aan licht wordt blootgesteld, het colloïde bindmiddel doet verharden. Onverharde delen kunnen worden afgewassen of weggeschuurd. Het pigment kan worden aangebracht vóór de belichting, of tijdens het ontwikkelen. Hoewel men aan de term dichromaat in de scheikunde tegenwoordig de voorkeur geeft, blijft bichromaat in gebruik in de fotografie.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052394/Dictionary of Photography (1965)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種沖印照片的技法，係利用重鉻酸鹽的特性，此種化合物受光照後可黏著的膠質部分會硬化，未硬化的部分可經由沖洗或磨蝕去除，而色料可在曝光前或顯影過程中加入。雖然化學中多稱為「二鉻酸鹽」（dichromate），但在攝影領域中一般仍稱為「重鉻酸鹽」（bichromate）。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
